  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.7,
      "text": "This is a LibriVox recording.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 2.62,
      "end": 4.78,
      "text": "Our LibriVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 5.64,
      "end": 11.44,
      "text": "For more information and to find out how you can volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 12.5,
      "end": 16.14,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, The Bear, and The Travelers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.0,
      "end": 21.06,
      "text": "Two travelers were on the road together when a bear suddenly appeared on the scene.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 21.9,
      "end": 27.66,
      "text": "Before he observed them, one made for a tree at the side of the road and climbed up into the branches and hid there.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 27.66,
      "end": 35.36,
      "text": "The other was not so nimble as his companion, and as he could not escape, he threw himself on the ground and pretended to be dead.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 36.22,
      "end": 40.98,
      "text": "The bear came up and sniffed all around him, but he kept perfectly still and held his breath.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 41.68,
      "end": 43.84,
      "text": "For they say that a bear will not touch a dead body.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 44.7,
      "end": 46.84,
      "text": "The bear took him for a corpse and went away.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 47.66,
      "end": 55.24,
      "text": "When the coast was clear, the traveler in the tree came down and asked the other what it was the bear had whispered to him when he put his mouth to his ear.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 55.24,
      "end": 62.56,
      "text": "The other replied, he told me never again to travel with a friend who deserts you at the first sign of danger.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 63.64,
      "end": 66.82,
      "text": "Ms. Forstian tests the sincerity of friendship.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 67.86,
      "end": 72.08,
      "text": "End of ASOP Fable, The Bear, and The Traveler.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
